Your project uses **MSTest v3 (3.8.0)** on net8.0. The latest is **MSTest 4.1.0**.

## Breaking changes that affect YOUR code

**`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — This is the main issue. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

## Other breaking changes to be aware of (not in your code today)

| Change | Fix |
|--------|-----|
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| `[TestMethod("name")]` constructor changed | Use `[TestMethod(DisplayName = "name")]` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Just use `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains` gone | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `TestTimeout.Infinite` removed | Use `int.MaxValue` |
| Custom `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` removed | Override `ExecuteAsync` instead |

